{"questionId":"3298410","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the least squares regression curve of the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid method to find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> value at the minimum&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>89</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>62</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0641</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1107</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>, graph, completing the square</p>\n<p>(so least squares regression is) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>42</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3298410","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.16b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the least squares regression curve of the form I=kd2.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}